result.execSummary:
The defendant Cory Charles Crowell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cory Charles Crowell is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Cory Charles Crowell was found guilty of Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA:  Alexis S. Mckinley   DF ATTY:  Alex Stormont   DF:  Cory Charles Crowell appeared.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court in 15CF36.  State revokes the DJOC in 14CF58.  Court enters and finds the DE adjudicated Guilty of Ct. 1 in 14CF58.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights for 15CF36. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads Guilty to Ct 2 in 15CF36. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE adjudicated guilty of Ct 2 in 15CF36. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 1 in 15CF36. Sentencing arguments. Victim rights have been complied with.  DE makes statement.  Crt orders:

Ct. 1 in 14CF58
Ct. 1 in 14CF58 concurrent to Ct. 2 in 15CF36
- S/W 3 years probation with coditions
- It is hereby ordered,  that the DE have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the following named persons and/or locations,  Cassandra H.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- DE sentenced to 60 days in the St. Croix County Jail with 40 days stayed
- Huber for work release
- Court costs of $268.00 and $250 for DNA Surcharge
- DE to pay costs through DOC
- DE is eligible for expungment at the completion of probation
- DE to begin jail time 60 days from 06/09/15
